Quote: Though there are no other varieties which cover so wide an area, yet the ferns form such a  prominent feature in the Flora, that New Zealand is often termed `The Land of Ferns,' and a fern frond has been taken as its emblem.
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1910
Source: NZ Plants
Author: COCKAYNE
Vol / Page: 1
Edition:
Quote: The land of the `Maori and Moa,' as a poet has called our land, has long been famous from both the ethnological and zoological standpoints. ... But when it comes to the question of the plant-life there is a pause. To be sure, New Zealand is known as the land of ferns, and not without truth; yet this admired group is found nearly all the world over, and is really much less important than are plenty of the other indigenous plants.
